        "user": "What is a transformer (architecture)?",
        "assistant": "# Transformer Architecture\n\nA **Transformer** is a deep learning architecture introduced in the 2017 paper *\"Attention Is All You Need\"* by Vaswani et al. It revolutionized natural language processing and now powers models like GPT, BERT, T5, and most modern AI systems.\n\n## Core Innovation\n\nUnlike previous architectures (RNNs, LSTMs) that processed sequences word-by-word, Transformers process **entire sequences in parallel** using a mechanism called **self-attention**.\n\n## Key Components\n\n### 1. Self-Attention Mechanism\nEach token in a sequence \"attends to\" every other token, learning which ones are relevant. It computes three vectors per token:\n- **Query (Q)** — what this token is looking for\n- **Key (K)** — what this token offers\n- **Value (V)** — the actual content\n\nThe attention formula:\n$$\\text{Attention}(Q, K, V) = \\text{softmax}\\left(\\frac{QK^T}{\\sqrt{d_k}}\\right)V$$\n\n### 2. Multi-Head Attention\nRuns multiple attention operations in parallel, each learning different relationships (e.g., syntactic vs. semantic).\n\n### 3. Positional Encoding\nSince Transformers have no inherent sense of order, positional information is added to token embeddings (via sinusoidal functions or learned embeddings).\n\n### 4. Feed-Forward Networks\nAfter attention, each position passes through a small fully-connected network independently.\n\n### 5. Residual Connections & Layer Normalization\nHelp with gradient flow and training stability in deep networks.\n\n## Architecture Variants\n\n| Type | Examples | Use Case |\n|------|----------|----------|\n| **Encoder-only** | BERT, RoBERTa | Understanding (classification, embeddings) |\n| **Decoder-only** | GPT, LLaMA, Claude | Generation (chat, text completion) |\n| **Encoder-Decoder** | T5, BART | Translation, summarization |\n\n## Why It Matters\n\n- **Parallelizable** — trains much faster than RNNs on GPUs/TPUs\n- **Scales remarkably well** — performance keeps improving with more data and parameters\n- **Captures long-range dependencies** — attention can directly link distant tokens\n- **Domain-general** — now used for images (Vision Transformers), audio, protein folding (AlphaFold), and more\n\nThe Transformer is the foundation of nearly every state-of-the-art AI model today.",
        "usage": {
          "input": 31,
          "output": 821
        },
        "durationMs": 10360,
        "finishReason": "stop"
