        "user": "What is a transformer (architecture)?",
        "assistant": "# Transformer Architecture\n\nA **Transformer** is a deep learning architecture introduced in the 2017 paper *\"Attention Is All You Need\"* by Vaswani et al. It revolutionized natural language processing and now underlies models like GPT, BERT, T5, and many others — including those used in computer vision, audio, and multimodal AI.\n\n## Core Idea\n\nThe transformer relies entirely on a mechanism called **self-attention** to process sequences, eliminating the need for recurrence (RNNs) or convolution (CNNs). This allows it to:\n- Process all tokens in parallel (much faster training)\n- Capture long-range dependencies effectively\n- Scale extremely well with data and compute\n\n## Key Components\n\n### 1. **Input Embeddings + Positional Encoding**\nSince the model doesn't process tokens sequentially, it adds **positional encodings** (sinusoidal or learned) to embeddings so the model knows token order.\n\n### 2. **Self-Attention**\nFor each token, the model computes:\n- **Query (Q)**, **Key (K)**, and **Value (V)** vectors\n\nThe attention output is:\n\n$$\\text{Attention}(Q, K, V) = \\text{softmax}\\left(\\frac{QK^T}{\\sqrt{d_k}}\\right)V$$\n\nThis lets every token \"attend to\" every other token, weighing their relevance.\n\n### 3. **Multi-Head Attention**\nMultiple attention operations run in parallel (\"heads\"), each learning different relationships (syntactic, semantic, etc.), then concatenated.\n\n### 4. **Feed-Forward Networks**\nA position-wise MLP applied to each token independently.\n\n### 5. **Residual Connections & Layer Normalization**\nHelp with gradient flow and training stability.\n\n## Architecture Variants\n\n| Type | Examples | Use Case |\n|------|----------|----------|\n| **Encoder-only** | BERT, RoBERTa | Understanding tasks (classification, NER) |\n| **Decoder-only** | GPT, LLaMA, Claude | Text generation |\n| **Encoder-Decoder** | T5, BART, original Transformer | Translation, summarization |\n\n## Why It Matters\n\nTransformers became the backbone of modern AI because they:\n- Scale predictably with parameters and data\n- Generalize across modalities (text, images via ViT, audio, code)\n- Enable foundation models and large language models (LLMs)\n\nWould you like a deeper dive into any specific part — like how self-attention works mathematically, or how decoder-only models generate text?",
